[I] Samba Commander

[T] Samba Commander is a text mode SMB network commander. In SMBC,
[T] you can browse the local network or you can use the search
[T] function to find the files. You can also download/upload files
[T] and directories or create them both locally and remotely. SMBC
[T] has a resume function and supports UTF-8 characters.

[U] http://smbc.airm.net/en/index.php

[A] Rafal Michniewicz
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/network
[F] NOPARALLEL

[L] GPL
[V] 1.2.2

[D] f49a9ee79da18eee6d714283bf330feeedb3a34a30b9b889657290ae smbc-1.2.2.tgz https://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/smbc/

[ $prefix_auto = 1 ] && prefix=opt/samba && set_confopt

pkgprefix -t samba
var_append GCC_WRAPPER_APPEND ' ' "-I$(pkgprefix includedir samba) -L$(pkgprefix libdir samba)"
